<tr><td class="printline">
<span class="postbody">I'd like to start a thread and get a list of recommended non english language movies. There are great films being produced in other places. I mean, with literally hundreds of movies produced outside of the english speaking world there has to be at least a handful of gems each year. 
<br />

<br />
Make sure your recommended movie has english subtitles. Most of us only speak english after all.
<br />

<br />
Chinese movies - language cantonese/mandarin dual audio, subs: english, maybe others
<br />

<br />
Stormriders: An excellent kung fu flick. It is based off the comic book of the same name which is available in an english translation I believe. Excellent fight choreography along with great (for it's time) special effects and cgi. The plot is basically a power hungry warlord conquers most of the land. Seeking his future he finds a prophet. The prophet reveals a fortelling which states that his (the warlord) success will be atributed to Wind & Cloud and his downfall will aslo be atributed to Wind & Cloud. Of course, the downfall part is not revealed to the warlord till later into the movie. Thus the story sets in motion. A very excellent movie.
<br />

<br />
Infernal Affairs: This is a trilogy but the first one is the best. That's the only one I'd recommend. A gangster movie with plots within plots. Not hard to follow but I understand chinese. Your mileage may vary. I heard a US company had picked up the rights and is remaking this movie in the US. Sort of like La Femme Nikita. It is just a rumor at this point though. An undercover cop movie with a twist. Very big twist. I won't say what it is so you'd just have to watch it.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
</td></tr>
<br />
