<span class="postbody">The remake was called "The Man with One Red Shoe."  One of Tom Hanks' earlier works.  I found it to be an enjoyable and funny movie, but now that I know there's an original, I'll have to find it sometime.
<br />

<br />
I'll mention a couple:
<br />

<br />
La Femme Nikita - the original French movie by Luc Besson (known more for Leon aka The Professional and The Fifth Element.)  This movie is great.  The american remake, "Point of No Return" wasn't horrible, but it just can't compare.  Don't even get me started about that p.o.s. tv show.  Innocent, my ass.
<br />

<br />
The Brotherhood of the Wolf - more people have probably seen this one, being as it saw extensive release here in America.  However, as it is a foreign language movie, and it kicked several levels of ass, I'll mention it here for those that might've let it slip by.  Watch it.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
